## Finding: Toolkit Lacks First-Principles Coverage of AI Session Lifecycle Management

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: The Toolkit phase contains 10 skills: age, ai_tool_orchestration, ceo-brain, content_creation, content_waterfall, cost_aware_llm_pipeline, iterative_retrieval, personal_brand, strategic_compact, video_research. A cross-cutting toolkit for an AI-driven dev framework must own complete coverage of: (1) session state lifecycle, (2) tool selection and routing, (3) cost governance, (4) context management, (5) knowledge capture and reuse, (6) orchestration patterns, (7) gap analysis and self-improvement, (8) brand/output quality, (9) content multiplication, and (10) research workflows. First-principles decomposition of "what must a toolkit own?" reveals the following atomic responsibilities that have NO skills covering them:
- Skill versioning and deprecation management (no skill exists)
- Skill dependency mapping and load ordering (no skill exists)
- Skill quality metrics and validation (no skill exists — /skill-create generates files but doesn't validate quality)
- AGE implementation pipeline: converting AGE findings into actual deployed skills (the age SKILL.md describes the loop protocol but does NOT describe how to take a gaps.log and produce shipping skills)
- Cross-phase toolkit injection: how the toolkit injects itself into non-toolkit phases (no skill exists)
- Reverse skill audit: mechanism to determine whether existing skills are being triggered and used (no skill exists — /learn extracts patterns but there is no "are existing skills working?" audit)
### Proposed Resolution: New SKILL.md named "skill-lifecycle-manager" in toolkit phase. Trigger commands: "audit skill usage", "are my skills working?", "skill deprecation report". Scope: Tracks which skills have been triggered in recent sessions, identifies stale skills, enforces version metadata on all SKILL.md files, and runs quality checks (does the skill have trigger commands? completion criteria? a version?).
### Cross-Phase Impact: Without this, ALL phases accumulate dead skills that never trigger. Skills from Build, Secure, and Maintenance phases silently fail to activate while users assume coverage exists.

