## Finding: No Skill Covers the AGE Implementation Pipeline (Gap-to-Skill Conversion)

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: The "age" SKILL.md describes a 25-loop protocol for discovering gaps. The AGE-PROTOCOL.md (8-loop variant) describes discovery and solution-speccing. However, NEITHER document covers what happens AFTER a gaps.log is produced. There is no skill describing: how to prioritize gaps from the log, how to assign gaps to team members, how to create the actual SKILL.md file from a Builder-loop spec, how to validate the new skill works, and how to integrate it back into the framework. The /skill-create command generates skills from git history, not from gaps.log findings. This means AGE analysis produces specifications that die in the log file with no mechanical path to shipping.
### Proposed Resolution: New SKILL.md named "age-to-skill-pipeline" in toolkit phase. Trigger commands: "implement age findings", "ship gaps from gaps.log", "convert age spec to skill". Scope: Takes a gaps.log Builder-loop output, extracts P0/P1 specs, creates SKILL.md scaffolding from each spec, runs /skill-create validation, and appends to skills-index.md.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Every AGE analysis run on every phase (Build, Secure, Ship, etc.) produces a gaps.log. Without this pipeline, the entire AGE infrastructure is purely diagnostic — it discovers problems but has no mechanical resolution path.

