### Evidence: DORA (DevOps Research and Assessment) metrics are the industry standard for measuring software delivery performance: Deployment Frequency, Lead Time for Changes, Mean Time to Recovery (MTTR), Change Failure Rate. The toolkit phase as cross-cutting infrastructure should track or enable measurement of all four. Current state: no toolkit skill mentions DORA. cost_aware_llm_pipeline tracks AI cost but not delivery velocity. strategic_compact tracks context but not lead time. The AGE skill finds gaps but does not measure if fixes improved DORA metrics. The framework has no telemetry or measurement skill. By contrast, high-performing engineering organizations use DORA as a north star. A framework claiming to support professional software delivery must enable DORA measurement.
### Proposed Resolution: New SKILL.md named "delivery-metrics" in toolkit phase. Trigger commands: "what are our DORA metrics?", "measure delivery performance", "deployment frequency report". Scope: Teaches how to instrument the framework to capture the four DORA metrics using git history, deployment logs, and incident records. Includes a .agent/metrics/ data store convention and a /metrics command. Priority P1.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Ship phase (deployment frequency, change failure rate), Maintenance phase (MTTR), Build phase (lead time). Without measurement, the framework cannot demonstrate improvement over time.

