## Finding: Toolkit Has No Compliance or Audit Trail Capability (SOC2, ISO 27001 Deviation)

### Gap Type: INDUSTRY_DEVIATION
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: SOC2 Type II and ISO 27001 require: (1) evidence that AI tools handling sensitive data have appropriate access controls, (2) audit logs of AI-assisted decisions affecting production systems, (3) human review attestation for AI-generated code going to production, (4) data handling policies for code sent to external AI APIs. The toolkit as currently defined: sends code to external AI APIs (Claude, Gemini, GPT-4) with no guidance on data classification, has no audit log of AI-assisted decisions, has no "human review required" gate for AI-generated artifacts, and has no policy skill for acceptable AI tool use. For enterprise teams using this framework, the lack of compliance guidance creates liability. The security-reviewer agent focuses on code security, not AI usage compliance. This is a documented industry gap.
### Proposed Resolution: New SKILL.md named "ai-compliance-toolkit" in toolkit phase. Trigger commands: "AI compliance review", "audit AI usage", "SOC2 AI checklist". Scope: Covers data classification for AI API calls (what to never send to external AI), audit logging of AI-assisted decisions, human-in-the-loop gates for production-bound AI-generated code, and policy templates for acceptable AI tool use. Priority P1 for enterprise users, P3 for solo developers.
### Cross-Phase Impact: All phases. Any phase that sends code or data to external AI APIs has compliance exposure. Secure and Ship phases are highest risk.

