## Finding: Toolkit Versioning Has No Semantic Versioning Standard (SRE/Release Engineering Deviation)

### Gap Type: INDUSTRY_DEVIATION
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: Examining SKILL.md version metadata: content_waterfall is "Skill Version: 2.0 | Merged from: content_cascade + waterfall_content | Updated: January 26, 2026". ai_tool_orchestration is "Skill Version: 1.0 | Created: February 2026". personal_brand is "Skill Version: 1.0 | Created: January 20, 2026". cost_aware_llm_pipeline has no version header. iterative_retrieval has no version header. age has no version header. ceo-brain has no version header. strategic_compact has no version header. video_research has no version header. content_creation has no version header. 7 of 10 toolkit skills have NO version metadata. The 3 that do use inconsistent formats. Industry standard (semver.org) requires MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH format with defined semantics. Without versioning: users cannot know if a skill is stable or experimental, breaking changes cannot be communicated, and the skill-dependency system (proposed in Loop 2) cannot specify minimum version requirements.
### Proposed Resolution: Establish mandatory semver versioning for all SKILL.md files. Add `version`, `status` (stable/experimental/deprecated), and `breaking_changes` fields to the SKILL.md frontmatter standard. Retrofit all 10 toolkit skills. The /skill-create command must generate version-stamped skills. Priority P2.
### Cross-Phase Impact: All phases. Applies to all skills across the framework, not just toolkit. This is a framework-wide standards gap.

